ich used to redirect users to ```http://127.0.0.1:53682/auth```. Unfortunately, this change also wasn't documented in the change log.\r\n\r\nCould you add a flag to allow the user to supply an authentication token or the whole auth url?\r\n\r\n\r\n#### What is your rclone version (output from `rclone version`)\r\n```\r\nrclone v1.50.0\r\n- os/arch: windows/amd64\r\n- go version: go1.12.7\r\n```\r\n(built from source)\r\n\r\n#### Which OS you are using and how many bits (eg Windows 7, 64 bit)\r\nany\r\n\r\n\r\n####  Which cloud storage system are you using? (eg Google Drive)\r\ndrive (any with oauth)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### The command you were trying to run (eg `rclone copy /tmp remote:tmp`)\r\n```rclone -vv config create test-2 drive scope drive```\r\n\r\n\r\n#### A log from the command with the `-vv` flag (eg output from `rclone -vv copy /tmp remote:tmp`)\r\n```\r\n2019/10/29 14:51:03 DEBUG : rclone: Version \"v1.50.0\" starting with parameters [\"rclone\" \"-vv\" \"config\" \"create\" \"test-2\" \"drive\" \"scope\" \"drive\"]\r\n2019/10/29 14:51:03 DEBUG : Using config file from \"###\\\\.config\\\\rclone\\\\rclone.conf\"\r\nRemote config\r\nUse auto config?\r\n * Say Y if not sure\r\n * Say N if you are working on a remote or headless machine\r\nAuto confirm is set: answering Yes, override by setting config parameter config_is_local=false\r\n2019/10/29 14:51:03 DEBUG : Starting auth server on 127.0.0.1:53682\r\nIf your browser doesn't open automatically go to the following link: http://127.0.0.1:53682/auth?state=hg4yWMKdr5JnKAxHHxWvzw\r\nLog in and authorize rclone for access\r\nWaiting for code...\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/3686/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/3686/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"}]